  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - BARD</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>20-30 IN A WEEK - ILL OMEN</font> - <small>Ridley, Terris-Thule</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>Good afternoon bards,<br>
<br>
This strategy is for those of you with a little more tolerance for the mundane and the intelligence to run when you're getting beat.  This really does work but if you screw up, you'll be visiting your bind point a lot.<br>
<br>
Ok, for starters you need to get to Firiona Vie in Kunark and bind.  From there, exit the city and follow beach to your left and you will come to a giant Iksar statue at the outlet of a river.  (There are a lot of spiders that wander around here and some can see invis.  They run faster than SoW and some cast.  Don't let them see you.)  Follow the river up and then climb the waterfall and you'll zone into Ill Omen.  <br>
<br>
You'll need a few spells - DDD, Bellow, and Selo's.  Go find a nice shaman/druid/rander and get a SoW.  (Note, the speed will differ based on level of player so be warned.)  Now...there are effectively two areas which you can pick from for this guide in the low 20's:  the windmill area (along with everyone and their dog) or north of ruins #6 on eqatlas.com's map (around pos 2000 pos 2000).  After 25 or so, hunt the open area south of the ruins for charbones, conscripts, and warlords.<br>
<br>
Now for the fun.  You probably have not practiced your brass very high which will be a pain for the first level or two but it will go up quickly with this strategy.  Equip your horn, change to helicopter view and go find something.  Preferrably Battlemasters and Aggressors since the BM drop bracers for a FV ranger quest that gives decent armor.  Now, once you have a baddie on ya, hit the Walk button.  You will still be faster than them but not by much.  Simply sing DDD until you get the message Badguy winces.  If you don't see any messages, you're too far away - get closer.  The easiest way to adjust distances is to turn in a circle...tighter circles will get you closer. This takes practice to get the range correct.  (Note - CoD requires you to be in mob attack range and is therefore not used here).  Once the mob winces, bellow until DDD wears off.  Repeat.<br>
<br>
You can level reasonably fast like that.  The true power of this strategy however, is when you get your new mad skillz down.  You can then take 3, 4, 5 yellows and be getting 2-3 bubs per hour.  Same songs, just get your first baddie on you like you have been.  Then pass his buddies and they'll all jump in.  Run in a circle until they're all together and do just like you have been.  DDD, Bellow, Bellow, Bellow, Repeat.  You should see 3 or 4 of them wincing with a couple resists each time.  As each mob dies, the next one you target will have less and less because they've been getting eaten down by your DDD.  When you kill your last, heal if you've been hit and go again - we don't need any stinking mana!!!  <br>
<br>
Things to note - if you have a group chasing you, the last of each race will flee when low on hp.  For example, if you have 3 gobs...the first two will chase you til they die, the last will flee at about 15% health.  This is why you don't want to mix race types.  Trying to keep 3 sarnaks off while you stay in bellow range of your gob just gets messy.  Undead will chase you til they die so target them first if you pull a few.
<br><br>

This does take some practice and takes a while to kill stuff until your brass skill gets up there.  But once it does...you'll outlevel any Sarnak, Windmill, anything group.  Hotkeys will make your life easier.  And use the Frontier Mountains zone if you get in over your head.  The other bonus is you don't need good equipment.  I levelled with 3 pieces of banded and my horn.
		<br><br></p></td></tr>
